body:
The following example query uses `span.or` clauses to specify two
[term](span-term-ref) operator queries that search for documents
in which the `title` field has either `city` or `country`.

**Input:**

```javascript
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search" : {
      "span": {
        "or": {
          "clauses": [
            { "term": { "path": "title", "query": "city" } },
            { "term": { "path": "title", "query": "country" } }
          ],
        }
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 5
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1
    }
  }
])
```

**Output:**

```json
[
  { title: 'Country' },
  { title: 'City Lights' },
  { title: 'King & Country' },
  { title: 'Fat City' },
  { title: 'Atlantic City' }
]
```

MongoDB Search returns the documents that contain the search words `city` or
`country` in the `title` field, but not both in the same `title`.
